WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:04.103
You think we're gonna get
him back on those meds again?

00:04.105 --> 00:05.810
Are those for Pope?

00:05.812 --> 00:09.016
[Pounding]

00:09.018 --> 00:11.708
I was admiring this little
gem when we came in tonight.

00:11.710 --> 00:13.986
So what's this thing do?
About a buck 20? A buck 30?

00:13.988 --> 00:16.364
- Open road, I've done 140.
- Wow.

00:16.367 --> 00:18.423
Well, I really liked your
dad. He seems very cool.

00:18.425 --> 00:20.194
- And that pallet of money story, man...
- [Laughs]

00:20.196 --> 00:21.507
that was crazy.

00:21.509 --> 00:23.906
The other day, he freaked
when I moved his briefcase.

00:23.908 --> 00:26.667
All his classified documents and shit?

00:26.669 --> 00:28.365
How's living with your grandmother?

00:28.367 --> 00:29.384
It's okay.

00:29.386 --> 00:31.263
That's a lot of people to contend with

00:31.265 --> 00:33.899
- after just being you and your Mom.
- Yeah.

00:37.904 --> 00:39.422
Hi, Mom.

00:39.424 --> 00:41.691
Hi, baby.

00:41.693 --> 00:43.359
Renn?

00:43.361 --> 00:46.262
Shit. Hey. Hey! Hey.

00:46.264 --> 00:48.998
[Bottles thud, objects clatter]

00:52.148 --> 00:55.438
You did good. You got J
opening up about his family.

00:55.440 --> 00:59.155
♪♪

00:59.157 --> 01:05.061
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:05.063 --> 01:08.979
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:08.981 --> 01:11.702
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:14.878 --> 01:20.639
♪ One they know that I cannot take ♪

01:20.641 --> 01:24.098
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:24.100 --> 01:27.770
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:31.335 --> 01:33.779
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:33.781 --> 01:36.269
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:37.659 --> 01:41.454
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:41.456 --> 01:44.296
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:45.329 --> 01:49.425
♪ I've got a big
black, big black hole ♪

01:49.427 --> 01:53.299
♪ Got a big black hole inside of me ♪

01:53.301 --> 01:55.598
♪ Got a ♪

01:55.600 --> 01:58.501
[Indistinct conversations,
door buzzes in distance]

01:58.503 --> 02:01.570
♪♪

02:03.000 --> 02:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:15.213 --> 02:16.532
Paul: I'm doing 120 right now!

02:16.534 --> 02:18.854
Put on your big boy
pants, man! Let's see it!

02:18.856 --> 02:21.991
- 125! 130!
- [Laughs]

02:21.993 --> 02:24.193
- Floor it! Come on!
- No, no, no.

02:24.195 --> 02:27.757
[Both laugh]

02:27.759 --> 02:29.498
I couldn't do it!

02:29.500 --> 02:31.734
Whoo. Better than sex, huh?

02:31.736 --> 02:34.437
More like a heart attack. [Laughs]

02:34.439 --> 02:37.840
Wanna go again? Go!

02:37.842 --> 02:40.876
[Engine revving]

02:44.147 --> 02:47.216
[Door buzzes]

02:47.218 --> 02:48.777
[Radio chatter, indistinct conversations]

02:48.779 --> 02:52.454
Need to see if these guys
are in here. I've got, uh...

02:52.456 --> 02:54.430
I'm here for my son, Andrew Cody.

02:54.432 --> 02:56.741
I was told you were his parole officer.

02:56.743 --> 02:59.152
You want to let me know
why he was arrested?

02:59.154 --> 03:01.532
Flash incarceration. A warning.

03:01.534 --> 03:03.571
If he violates his parole again,

03:03.573 --> 03:05.521
he'll serve out the rest
of his sentence in prison.

03:05.523 --> 03:08.167
My son did not violate his parole.

03:08.169 --> 03:12.631
My son has a job, a home, and
he reports to you regularly.

03:12.633 --> 03:15.054
Maybe I should just call my lawyer.

03:15.056 --> 03:17.003
You wanna waste your money, you go ahead.

03:17.005 --> 03:19.504
There's nothing he can do
about a failed drug test.

03:19.506 --> 03:22.264
- Andrew does not take drugs.
- [Door closes in distance]

03:22.266 --> 03:25.354
Well, he must've taken something.

03:25.611 --> 03:27.156
Is he back on his meds?

03:27.158 --> 03:29.325
[Indistinct conversations]

03:30.552 --> 03:31.745
Sit down.

03:31.747 --> 03:33.329
He'll be released shortly.

03:33.331 --> 03:35.064
[Telephone ringing in distance]

03:36.376 --> 03:39.802
Happens again, he'll do real time.

03:39.804 --> 03:41.470
[Door buzzes]

03:41.717 --> 03:44.106
- I need those checked out.
- Man: All right.

03:44.108 --> 03:46.208
I'm saving up for college, for Nicky,

03:46.210 --> 03:47.777
if she ever goes.

03:47.779 --> 03:49.455
Lord knows schools aren't lining up

03:49.457 --> 03:51.180
- to admit "C" students right now.
- [Gear shifts, engine turns off]

03:51.182 --> 03:53.849
Oh, she'll get it
together. She's a smart kid.

04:00.542 --> 04:02.525
Oh, you can leave it in
there, man. I-I'll lock it.

04:02.527 --> 04:04.160
Oh, no, no, no. That's okay.

04:06.963 --> 04:09.998
My dad wants to know if
you want Mexican or Italian.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.367
Whatever's fine.

04:11.553 --> 04:12.418
I don't know what's worse...

04:12.420 --> 04:15.485
him hating you or inviting
you for family night. [Laughs]

04:15.487 --> 04:17.139
Oh, wait.

04:17.416 --> 04:20.055
The hotter you look, the
better mood Anderson'll be

04:20.058 --> 04:21.803
when she grades our tests.

04:21.805 --> 04:23.646
[Indistinct conversations]

04:23.648 --> 04:25.414
- [Bell ringing]
- Mm.

04:26.683 --> 04:28.384
Sit down, everyone.

04:28.386 --> 04:31.984
Ms. Anderson is out. I'm giving the test.

04:31.986 --> 04:33.987
[Singsongy] Looks like it's my turn.

04:33.989 --> 04:35.724
Think he'll give me any of the answers?

04:35.726 --> 04:37.660
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

04:37.662 --> 04:39.995
[Indistinct conversations]

04:40.462 --> 04:42.415
Pass it back.

04:43.175 --> 04:44.465
Pass it back.

04:44.467 --> 04:46.219
_

04:46.221 --> 04:47.922
Pass it back.

04:49.152 --> 04:50.518
_

04:50.520 --> 04:52.326
Pass it back.

05:01.051 --> 05:04.041
- [Cellphone chimes and vibrates]
- [Sighs]

05:04.043 --> 05:06.589
Take a shower, put on
your wire, go to school.

05:06.591 --> 05:09.391
- He trusts me.
- Good.

05:09.648 --> 05:12.962
Look, I can't do this. I
can't... I can't even sleep.

05:13.286 --> 05:14.647
Where was this conscience when you decided

05:14.649 --> 05:17.175
to buy 5 grams of heroin
from an undercover cop?

05:17.177 --> 05:20.500
- I've never done this before, okay?
- I need details...

05:20.502 --> 05:22.197
what the Codys did,
what they're doing next.

05:22.199 --> 05:23.610
What am I supposed to say?

05:23.612 --> 05:25.627
Seriously? What am I supposed to say?

05:25.629 --> 05:26.996
"Hey, J, how's it going?

05:26.998 --> 05:29.781
By the way, what crimes have
your family been up to lately?"

05:29.783 --> 05:32.209
I'm the only thing keeping
your life from blowing up.

05:32.211 --> 05:33.743
You should be thanking me.

05:35.370 --> 05:37.720
You <i>should</i> be thanking me.

05:37.990 --> 05:40.289
Thank you.

05:40.596 --> 05:42.524
Put your shoes on.

05:42.754 --> 05:45.094
I'm gonna show you something.

05:47.864 --> 05:49.265
[Door opens]

05:49.267 --> 05:50.833
I need some advice.

05:50.835 --> 05:52.815
What do you do when your
daughter's screaming nonstop

05:52.817 --> 05:54.295
because you won't let
her get her ears pierced?

05:54.297 --> 05:57.471
- I mean, what do you do?
- [Chuckles] How old is she?

05:57.473 --> 05:59.521
6. [Laughs]

05:59.523 --> 06:02.193
But her mother's were pierced
before she was on solids.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.824
It's a Latina thing. I don't know.

06:03.826 --> 06:06.228
- You, my friend, are screwed.
- [Laughs]

06:06.230 --> 06:08.017
All right? So just accept it.

06:08.019 --> 06:11.353
Raise up that white flag
and... and just, you know,

06:11.780 --> 06:13.422
- avoid all the tantrums.
- Yeah.

06:13.424 --> 06:16.091
Focus on the family
business. That's what I say.

06:16.326 --> 06:17.830
How's that going, anyway?

06:17.832 --> 06:19.448
It's good. Yeah, it's good.

06:19.450 --> 06:21.794
I mean, it's better than
working for someone else.

06:21.796 --> 06:25.288
I spent two years keeping the
books for Elite Platinum Properties.

06:25.290 --> 06:27.882
Basically just a fancy name
for a shithead named Artie.

06:27.884 --> 06:30.551
- [Laughs]
- I'm telling you,

06:30.553 --> 06:32.816
I kept his business running
while he made his tee time.

06:32.818 --> 06:33.719
I deserved to be partner.

06:33.721 --> 06:36.819
All I asked for was a raise,
said he couldn't justify it.

06:36.821 --> 06:39.218
- What'd you do?
- Well, I waited till tax time,

06:39.220 --> 06:41.896
then I dumped a year's worth
of invoices on his desk.

06:41.898 --> 06:43.385
First, he shit a brick. Then he, uh...

06:43.387 --> 06:45.854
- [Laughs]
- ...then he begged me to stay.

06:46.123 --> 06:47.209
What'd you say?

06:47.211 --> 06:48.991
Well, I said, I couldn't justify it.

06:48.993 --> 06:50.359
[Both laugh]

06:50.361 --> 06:51.923
- [Bottles clink]
- Cheers.

06:51.925 --> 06:53.829
What about you?

06:54.073 --> 06:56.106
You ever feel like giving
your boss the finger?

06:57.067 --> 06:58.867
- Who hasn't?
- Yeah.

06:59.040 --> 07:00.740
What would you do?

07:02.373 --> 07:05.441
You know, to get back at
him. What would you do?

07:06.177 --> 07:07.949
Come on. Tell me you
haven't thought about it.

07:07.951 --> 07:10.212
- I call bullshit.
- Two beers?

07:10.214 --> 07:12.348
- Here you go.
- [Bottles thud]

07:12.350 --> 07:13.816
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

07:13.818 --> 07:17.680
[Indistinct conversations]

07:17.682 --> 07:21.433
Maybe I would, uh, adjust the paperwork,

07:21.435 --> 07:24.073
so all the ATMs on the
<i>U.S.S Ronald Reagan</i>

07:24.075 --> 07:25.560
would run out of cash

07:25.562 --> 07:27.763
about three months into their deployment.

07:27.765 --> 07:28.949
- [Laughs]
- Right?

07:28.951 --> 07:31.364
I'd bury... I would
bury all the shortcomings

07:31.366 --> 07:33.268
and I'd make it completely untraceable.

07:33.270 --> 07:36.663
Ah. But wouldn't that get you in trouble?

07:36.665 --> 07:38.073
Not if I did it right.

07:38.075 --> 07:40.109
Shit would roll uphill
with that kind of money.

07:40.111 --> 07:43.814
[Laughs] You could make
that much money go missing?

07:43.816 --> 07:45.114
Are you kidding me?

07:45.116 --> 07:47.440
That kind of money goes
missing all the time.

07:47.442 --> 07:49.551
The Navy just doesn't want
anybody to know about it.

07:49.553 --> 07:52.554
<i>♪♪</i>

07:57.699 --> 07:58.914
LSD.

07:58.916 --> 08:00.404
There must've been some mistake.

08:00.406 --> 08:01.463
That's what I told my P.O.

08:01.465 --> 08:03.601
I've never taken that shit in my life.

08:03.603 --> 08:06.796
- Are you sure this wasn't a shakedown?
- No, he's straight.

08:06.798 --> 08:08.932
"Piss test don't lie." That's what he said.

08:08.934 --> 08:10.172
Well, that's not true.

08:10.174 --> 08:11.704
They mix up those samples all the time.

08:11.706 --> 08:13.707
They made me take a second test.

08:13.709 --> 08:15.642
- [Cellphone chimes]
- It's positive.

08:18.779 --> 08:20.273
- That's Baz. He wants to meet.
- [Buzzer]

08:20.275 --> 08:21.717
He's been working on an idea.

08:21.719 --> 08:24.686
[Engine idling]

08:27.717 --> 08:29.334
You comin'?

08:33.328 --> 08:35.330
[Engine turns off]

08:35.332 --> 08:38.000
Used to be a house down there.

08:38.394 --> 08:41.870
Emilio and Carmen Ortiz.

08:42.044 --> 08:45.574
Used to work with me
back when I was on patrol.

08:45.576 --> 08:47.242
Cops?

08:47.244 --> 08:49.211
Confidential informants.

08:55.538 --> 08:57.889
They had done a string of
robberies along the coast

08:57.891 --> 08:59.521
and wanted out.

08:59.895 --> 09:02.201
I think they would've been okay
after they did a little time,

09:02.203 --> 09:03.406
- but...
- [Latch clanks, dog barking in distance]

09:03.408 --> 09:04.915
...they made the mistake
of getting into business

09:04.917 --> 09:07.521
- with Janine Cody.
- [Helicopter whirring overhead]

09:07.523 --> 09:09.798
J's grandmother.

09:09.800 --> 09:12.214
She suspected they were informants,

09:12.216 --> 09:14.816
sent her son Andrew to burn the house down.

09:17.386 --> 09:19.237
They found Carmen here.

09:21.397 --> 09:24.091
She was lucky. She died of smoke inhalation

09:24.093 --> 09:26.482
before her skin started to burn off.

09:26.870 --> 09:29.852
Could only confirm it was her
after we sent the teeth to the lab.

09:30.236 --> 09:34.147
And Emilio... he must've tried to run.

09:34.149 --> 09:36.352
Found him by the door.

09:36.354 --> 09:40.062
Part of the burning ceiling
fell, severed his torso.

09:40.064 --> 09:42.998
March 3, 1997.

09:46.060 --> 09:49.505
So the last people to
inform on the Codys for you

09:49.507 --> 09:52.141
burned to death.

09:52.143 --> 09:54.843
And you want me to get
J to do the same thing?

09:54.845 --> 09:58.480
He's not one of them. Not really.

09:58.482 --> 10:01.350
And this is what they do to outsiders.

10:01.352 --> 10:05.053
Only way to protect him is
to get him away from them.

10:05.055 --> 10:06.488
But how?

10:06.490 --> 10:08.590
Keep doing what you're doing.

10:08.592 --> 10:10.092
[Sighs]

10:14.797 --> 10:16.932
He kissed me.

10:18.468 --> 10:20.536
Text him.

10:20.538 --> 10:22.641
See what he's doing after school.

10:23.973 --> 10:27.567
Are you asking me to sleep
with a 17-year-old kid?

10:27.569 --> 10:30.345
Of course not. That would be illegal.

10:32.382 --> 10:36.214
But if you care about
that kid, get him out,

10:36.216 --> 10:38.550
before we have to ID
<i>him</i> by his teeth.

10:47.610 --> 10:50.377
You, uh, holding out on me?

10:50.379 --> 10:51.783
I didn't do LSD.

10:51.785 --> 10:54.322
- Hey, you eat a bagel?
- What?

10:54.324 --> 10:56.976
- A bagel. Did you eat a bagel?
- What the hell are you talking about?

10:56.978 --> 10:58.933
The poppy seeds, man.
That shit is in your piss.

10:58.935 --> 11:01.106
- Everybody knows that.
- Craig: Come on.

11:01.108 --> 11:02.554
That's opium, dipshit.

11:02.556 --> 11:03.547
Yeah, well, maybe something else.

11:03.549 --> 11:05.599
Maybe not the poppies, but, you know,

11:05.601 --> 11:08.556
something like that. Just sayin'.

11:08.558 --> 11:09.991
To your health.

11:09.993 --> 11:11.960
[Clears throat]

11:11.962 --> 11:13.561
Hey.

11:13.563 --> 11:15.630
Craig: Pope spent the night in jail.

11:15.632 --> 11:17.365
Yeah, I heard.

11:17.367 --> 11:19.988
Not even long enough to make
a toothbrush into a shiv.

11:19.990 --> 11:23.267
- Smurf: Okay, let's get started.
- I think I have something.

11:23.269 --> 11:25.974
Could be big.

11:25.976 --> 11:28.636
Camp Pendleton.

11:28.638 --> 11:30.880
- Wow, what about it?
- We're gonna hit it.

11:30.882 --> 11:32.839
That's a military base.

11:32.841 --> 11:34.593
Sounds awesome. I'm in.

11:34.595 --> 11:37.340
Yeah, what are we going for?
A nuclear warhead or a tank?

11:37.342 --> 11:40.556
There is a ton of cash on that base. A ton.

11:40.558 --> 11:44.546
Surrounded by soldiers with sniper
rifles and attack helicopters.

11:44.548 --> 11:47.006
Yeah, all useless if they
don't know we're taking it.

11:47.008 --> 11:48.262
How?

11:48.583 --> 11:49.887
Still working on that part.

11:49.889 --> 11:51.959
Well, sounds like a foolproof plan.

11:51.961 --> 11:53.362
Look, it's gonna take some time,

11:53.364 --> 11:54.902
but my mark knows the
ins and outs of the base.

11:54.904 --> 11:57.295
- Wait, your mark?
- Yeah. Paul.

11:57.297 --> 11:58.671
Nicky's dad.

11:58.673 --> 12:00.998
Nicky? J's girlfriend Nicky?

12:01.000 --> 12:03.295
Yeah. He handles serious
money for long deployments,

12:03.297 --> 12:06.695
aircraft carriers, all that.
I've been workin' him hard.

12:06.697 --> 12:09.583
Hold on. Since when do
we do jobs with people

12:09.585 --> 12:12.351
outside of the family?

12:12.353 --> 12:14.904
This Paul guy... he sounds like a pussy.

12:14.906 --> 12:17.843
And the... the second the
cops breathe in his direction,

12:17.845 --> 12:19.394
he's going to point them right to us.

12:19.396 --> 12:21.418
Pope, I can handle him.

12:21.420 --> 12:23.768
I got a feeling he's ready
to cross a line. He wants it.

12:23.770 --> 12:25.523
- He just needs a push. I'm telling you...
- No.

12:25.525 --> 12:28.569
No! No! No.

12:28.932 --> 12:32.087
We case a joint, we go in with guns,

12:32.089 --> 12:33.701
we come out with cash.

12:33.703 --> 12:35.002
It's not that complicated.

12:35.004 --> 12:38.822
Like the Wells Fargo job? So
easy it landed you in prison.

12:38.824 --> 12:41.215
Yeah. Saving your ass.

12:41.217 --> 12:44.552
[Inhales and exhales deeply]

12:45.155 --> 12:47.188
Are you on board with this crap?

12:51.216 --> 12:53.418
Let's see if the plan has legs.

12:58.067 --> 12:59.600
[Cup thuds]

13:04.853 --> 13:06.425
Gonna need you guys to do your part.

13:06.427 --> 13:08.376
Yeah, I got an opening in my
schedule on Thursday, so...

13:08.378 --> 13:10.111
It's gotta be tonight.

13:10.441 --> 13:12.780
- Renn's throwing a party.
- Well, you're missing it.

13:12.782 --> 13:13.700
[Exhales]

13:13.702 --> 13:16.096
I'll give you the details in a minute.

13:17.840 --> 13:19.378
Is that your way of telling us to leave?

13:19.380 --> 13:20.888
Mm-hmm.

13:20.890 --> 13:22.857
[Chairs scrape floor]

13:26.267 --> 13:29.803
Pope suspect anything? Meds?

13:29.805 --> 13:31.302
I don't know.

13:31.304 --> 13:32.779
What about J?

13:32.781 --> 13:34.089
What <i>about</i> J?

13:34.091 --> 13:36.724
He might have an opinion
on using Nicky's dad.

13:36.726 --> 13:39.186
J will find out when I want him to.

13:39.188 --> 13:41.097
Good. We agree.

13:41.099 --> 13:44.712
No, we don't agree.

13:44.893 --> 13:47.512
You're talking about a military base.

13:49.017 --> 13:50.610
You, too, huh?

13:50.612 --> 13:52.939
The bigger the score, the bigger the risk.

13:52.941 --> 13:54.813
But not if we do it my way.

13:59.628 --> 14:01.896
[Gears shift]

14:01.898 --> 14:03.831
[Engine turns off]

14:16.779 --> 14:18.913
[Door squeaks]

14:36.298 --> 14:37.598
[Bag rustling]

14:41.370 --> 14:44.405
[Rustling continues]

14:53.782 --> 14:56.100
<i>[TV playing indistinctly]</i>

14:56.102 --> 14:58.520
Whoo! I'm making you my bitch.

14:58.522 --> 14:59.487
[Bubbling]

14:59.489 --> 15:03.320
[Inhales sharply] Yeah, Baz
is making us both his bitches.

15:03.322 --> 15:06.828
Well, if his idea works, at
least we'll be rolling in it.

15:07.214 --> 15:08.626
You know, we could rob Fort Knox,

15:08.628 --> 15:10.983
and Smurf would still have us on allowance.

15:10.985 --> 15:12.444
This is bullshit.

15:12.446 --> 15:14.635
I could be at a killer party right now.

15:14.637 --> 15:15.929
Yeah, and robbing a house would be rad

15:15.931 --> 15:18.673
- if Baz doesn't make us do all the work.
- Mm-hmm.

15:18.675 --> 15:21.108
<i>[TV continues indistinctly]</i>

15:21.394 --> 15:23.194
What's up?

15:23.196 --> 15:25.524
Just waiting for Smurf.

15:25.526 --> 15:26.999
What, are you going to church?

15:27.001 --> 15:29.274
No. I'm going to dinner
with Nicky's family.

15:29.276 --> 15:33.321
Well, if her dad's paying, get the lobster.

15:33.323 --> 15:35.004
[Rack clatters]

15:35.006 --> 15:37.792
Shouldn't you boys be getting a move on?

15:37.958 --> 15:40.561
Yeah, after this game.

15:40.739 --> 15:43.598
J, can you wait for me in the car, please?

15:43.600 --> 15:46.434
<i>[TV continues indistinctly]</i>

15:50.417 --> 15:55.343
I want you to go <i>now</i> and focus.

15:55.512 --> 15:56.707
Look, if you don't think we're capable

15:56.709 --> 15:59.640
of doing this job, you can
go find someone else to do it.

15:59.642 --> 16:01.860
Baby, I would never ask you to do anything

16:01.862 --> 16:05.196
- you feel uncomfortable with.
- Craig: Good.

16:05.198 --> 16:06.690
- Then tell Baz we're taking
- [Balls rattle]

16:06.692 --> 16:08.850
the night off from his bullshit.

16:08.852 --> 16:10.385
Go.

16:12.594 --> 16:13.995
[Pool stick thuds]

16:14.324 --> 16:16.342
You really feel that way?

16:16.344 --> 16:18.110
Mm-hmm.

16:21.344 --> 16:23.012
Deran?

16:23.014 --> 16:24.814
Tell her, man.

16:29.841 --> 16:31.689
Pussy!

16:34.688 --> 16:37.718
I think Pope will be
happy to fill in for you.

16:39.288 --> 16:41.318
And I'll remember who pulled their weight

16:41.320 --> 16:43.554
when I divvy up the take.

16:48.597 --> 16:50.431
- [Sea birds calling in distance]
- Cath?

16:53.325 --> 16:54.837
Cath.

16:56.285 --> 16:57.751
Hey.

16:59.382 --> 17:01.842
We waited for you, but Lena was tired.

17:01.844 --> 17:04.512
Yeah, I got held up at Smurf's.

17:04.580 --> 17:06.347
I called.

17:06.348 --> 17:08.549
Deran said you left hours ago.

17:12.415 --> 17:15.021
You think I like this?

17:15.172 --> 17:18.056
The nagging wife, always
asking where you've been.

17:18.058 --> 17:19.627
Well, you're getting good at it.

17:19.628 --> 17:21.944
[Object thuds]

17:21.946 --> 17:25.378
You know, guys come into the
bar and hit on me all the time.

17:25.381 --> 17:28.234
[Paper rustles]

17:28.435 --> 17:31.605
I'm not cheating on you, Cath. Okay?

17:33.847 --> 17:35.710
Used to be a pain in the ass,

17:35.818 --> 17:38.888
trying to let them down
gently without losing tips.

17:40.021 --> 17:42.483
Now I look forward to it,

17:42.606 --> 17:44.819
someone wanting to talk to me.

17:45.689 --> 17:47.388
I was at my dad's.

17:48.115 --> 17:50.324
He lives in a trailer over in Vista.

17:52.194 --> 17:54.462
I thought he was in for life.

17:54.862 --> 17:57.965
I guess the state thought
26 years was enough.

17:58.153 --> 17:59.667
You're talking to him?

17:59.801 --> 18:01.634
After everything he did to you...

18:06.668 --> 18:08.175
You telling me you wouldn't
talk to your parents

18:08.255 --> 18:10.122
if they were still alive?

18:13.482 --> 18:15.216
Does Smurf know?

18:15.218 --> 18:17.651
[Chuckles]

18:17.801 --> 18:20.955
No. No, Smurf does not know.

18:22.383 --> 18:26.127
Doesn't matter anyway. He's gone.

18:26.129 --> 18:27.387
Where?

18:27.389 --> 18:30.757
Who knows? But he's gone.

18:34.243 --> 18:35.836
Then why'd you go there?

18:36.697 --> 18:38.562
Feed his cat.

18:39.908 --> 18:43.177
- [Laughs]
- [Laughs]

18:43.179 --> 18:46.733
You... You went to feed his cat?

18:46.735 --> 18:49.984
I did. Yes. [Chuckles]

18:59.494 --> 19:02.863
<i>♪♪</i>

19:02.865 --> 19:04.532
[Laughs]

19:04.534 --> 19:07.168
- Salud.
- Man: Salud.

19:07.170 --> 19:08.669
[Glass thuds]

19:08.671 --> 19:10.371
[Glass thuds]

19:10.373 --> 19:13.908
I had no idea the shit
in Fresno was this good.

19:13.910 --> 19:15.322
- [Laughs]
- [Clears throat]

19:15.324 --> 19:17.407
You should have your
cousins come down more often.

19:17.409 --> 19:20.167
You ready for another line?

19:20.169 --> 19:22.704
I don't have to be
anywhere. [Exhales deeply]

19:22.706 --> 19:23.580
You know, if you'd told me

19:23.582 --> 19:26.395
this is what you do after
you close... [Sniffs]

19:26.397 --> 19:28.405
- I would've been here every night.
- [Glass thuds]

19:28.407 --> 19:30.958
- [Both laugh]
- Scottie manages the place.

19:30.960 --> 19:32.924
[Sniffs]

19:32.926 --> 19:34.728
Mm.

19:34.730 --> 19:36.464
Whoa! Whoo!

19:36.466 --> 19:39.133
- Whoo!
- [Laughter]

19:40.937 --> 19:44.472
[Lowered voice] Now I
want you to make me scream.

19:44.614 --> 19:45.980
Hmm.

19:54.916 --> 19:56.750
♪♪

19:56.752 --> 19:58.018
All right.

19:58.020 --> 19:59.620
[Phantogram's "You Don't
Get Me High Anymore" playing]

19:59.622 --> 20:01.922
[Breathing heavily]

20:01.924 --> 20:04.158
♪ I don't like staying at home ♪

20:04.160 --> 20:06.460
♪ When the moon is bleeding red ♪

20:06.462 --> 20:09.079
♪ Woke up stoned in the
backseat from a dream ♪

20:09.081 --> 20:11.429
♪ Where my teeth fell out of my head ♪

20:11.431 --> 20:13.535
♪ Do you feel like letting go? ♪

20:13.537 --> 20:16.070
[Whispers] Now come here.

20:16.302 --> 20:21.942
♪ I wonder how far down it is ♪

20:21.944 --> 20:23.366
[Both breathing heavily]

20:23.368 --> 20:25.513
♪ Nothing is fun ♪

20:25.515 --> 20:28.215
♪ Not like before ♪

20:28.217 --> 20:31.819
♪ You don't get me high anymore ♪

20:31.821 --> 20:33.120
[Both panting]

20:33.122 --> 20:35.623
♪ Used to take one ♪

20:35.625 --> 20:37.791
♪ Now it takes four ♪

20:37.793 --> 20:42.796
♪ You don't get me high anymore ♪

20:42.798 --> 20:45.444
♪♪

20:45.446 --> 20:48.549
♪ You don't get me high anymore ♪

20:51.902 --> 20:54.271
Can't believe Smurf has me doing this shit.

20:54.273 --> 20:55.902
It's not Smurf. It's Baz.

20:55.904 --> 20:59.698
I haven't hit a house since, like, puberty.

20:59.700 --> 21:02.025
Jeez, man, you were bitching
about the job being too hard.

21:02.027 --> 21:04.521
Now you're bitching
about it being too easy.

21:04.628 --> 21:06.970
- Why you even here?
- Do you wanna do it alone?

21:06.972 --> 21:09.945
- Do you?
- Relax, man. No.

21:09.947 --> 21:12.372
One night in jail and
you're in a shitty mood.

21:12.374 --> 21:15.932
Something happens tonight...

21:16.167 --> 21:19.769
I'm coming out firing.
Do you understand me?

21:19.954 --> 21:23.608
They're gonna have to kill me
'cause I'm not going back inside.

21:25.163 --> 21:27.010
Jesus, man, what happened to you in there?

21:27.012 --> 21:31.214
[Engine starts, shifts gears]

21:31.216 --> 21:35.051
♪♪

21:39.090 --> 21:42.158
♪♪

21:45.296 --> 21:47.597
- [Beeping]
- Pope: Bingo. Magnet.

21:52.203 --> 21:54.337
[Clicking]

21:54.339 --> 21:57.641
♪♪

21:57.643 --> 21:59.009
Pope: All right, TV.

21:59.011 --> 22:02.145
♪♪

22:13.658 --> 22:16.192
What do you say

22:16.194 --> 22:19.369
we do some more blow and go again?

22:19.371 --> 22:21.891
- Hmm?
- Tempting.

22:21.893 --> 22:24.100
But I gotta go.

22:24.481 --> 22:26.536
I don't wanna see this.

22:26.538 --> 22:28.193
See what?

22:28.195 --> 22:31.976
- [Bottle clinks]
- See what?

22:31.978 --> 22:34.732
Sage was in Portland the day I got robbed.

22:34.734 --> 22:37.665
Showed me a plane ticket and everything.

22:37.667 --> 22:39.649
It's an easy mistake.

22:39.898 --> 22:41.662
You don't have to feel bad.
We'll find the right guy.

22:41.664 --> 22:43.773
You had my necklace...

22:44.819 --> 22:48.058
the one you said you got from him.

22:48.060 --> 22:51.494
You left me to die, Craig.

22:51.496 --> 22:53.963
Now I'm gonna do the same.

22:53.965 --> 22:56.199
Aah!

22:56.201 --> 22:59.736
[Men grunting]

22:59.738 --> 23:01.304
Scottie: Tie this piece of shit.

23:01.306 --> 23:03.406
- Got it?
- I got it, got it.

23:03.408 --> 23:05.709
[Grunts]

23:05.711 --> 23:10.013
- Come on.
- [Craig grunting]

23:10.015 --> 23:11.581
[Chair scrapes floor]

23:14.585 --> 23:16.886
Come on. Let's get him up.

23:16.888 --> 23:19.923
[Grunting]

23:23.227 --> 23:25.829
[Zipties creaking]

23:25.831 --> 23:28.798
Uhh!

23:28.800 --> 23:30.974
I got the jewelry from
the bedroom, but it's crap.

23:30.976 --> 23:32.890
It won't even cover the cost of gas.

23:32.892 --> 23:35.560
Yeah, who gives a shit?
I got the briefcase.

23:35.562 --> 23:36.775
What's in it?

23:36.777 --> 23:38.826
I don't know. Papers and stuff.

23:38.828 --> 23:41.042
Papers? Baz has us breaking in for papers?

23:41.044 --> 23:42.548
Yeah.

23:42.550 --> 23:43.997
You wanna tell me why I'm wasting my time

23:43.999 --> 23:46.281
for a used television and crap jewelry?

23:46.283 --> 23:48.805
Look, I don't know, man.
I'm just doing what I'm told.

23:48.807 --> 23:50.307
Pope: All right, let's get out of here.

23:52.323 --> 23:53.757
[Glass shatters]

23:53.759 --> 23:57.694
[Alarm blaring, dog barking in distance]

23:57.696 --> 23:59.229
Come on, come on.

23:59.231 --> 24:01.924
Okay, so, uh, two strawberries,

24:01.926 --> 24:05.187
a cookies and cream. Nicky,
I know you want mint chip. J?

24:05.189 --> 24:06.572
- Chocolate, please.
- And chocolate.

24:06.574 --> 24:07.871
This is so lame.

24:07.873 --> 24:09.785
- He's fine. He's being nice.
- Okay, so that's...

24:09.787 --> 24:11.385
- Uh, Paul.
- That's $5.

24:11.387 --> 24:13.080
- No, no, no. Your money's no good here.
- No, no, come on, I...

24:13.082 --> 24:14.780
No, no, no. Your uncle
bought me lunch today.

24:14.782 --> 24:19.449
Tonight is on me. Okay?
Baz. He took care of me.

24:19.451 --> 24:22.018
Thank you. No, you guys keep
the change. Thank you so much.

24:22.020 --> 24:23.672
How boring are we?

24:23.674 --> 24:25.622
- [Cellphone rings]
- [Laughs] Right?

24:25.624 --> 24:27.023
- [Ring]
- Oh.

24:27.025 --> 24:28.892
- [Beep]
- Yeah?

24:31.028 --> 24:33.897
Thank you.

24:33.899 --> 24:35.830
- We gotta go.
- [Beep]

24:35.832 --> 24:37.705
No, we gotta go right now.

24:48.223 --> 24:49.623
That H?

24:55.712 --> 24:57.387
Four dimes.

24:57.677 --> 24:59.645
Enough to OD an elephant.

25:03.713 --> 25:07.330
You guys don't think
I'm buying this, do you?

25:07.332 --> 25:09.699
Huh?

25:11.035 --> 25:12.702
Get the plastic.

25:12.704 --> 25:15.271
Sure, get the plastic.

25:15.273 --> 25:17.373
Good idea. Mm-hmm.

25:23.581 --> 25:27.157
Okay. Okay, l-look...
m-message received, okay?

25:27.159 --> 25:28.860
I was an asshole. So
give me a good beating,

25:28.862 --> 25:31.496
and we'll call it even, okay?

25:32.690 --> 25:34.424
Scottie: Where do we dump his body?

25:34.426 --> 25:35.006
- Arrowhead?
- [Zipties clacking]

25:35.008 --> 25:38.394
Look, it wasn't my fault, okay? I...

25:38.396 --> 25:42.075
I-I checked Renn's... I checked
her... I checked her pulse.

25:42.077 --> 25:43.964
I'm not a goddamn doctor.

25:43.966 --> 25:46.271
Wait. Wait. Wait, wait! Wait, wait, wait!

25:46.273 --> 25:48.609
Do you know who my family is? Huh?

25:48.611 --> 25:51.422
If you do anything to me,
you're signing your own...

25:51.424 --> 25:53.403
You are signing your own death certificate!

25:53.405 --> 25:55.371
No! No!

25:55.373 --> 25:57.495
No, call 9-1-1!
No, no, no!

25:57.497 --> 25:59.857
Come on, don't... don't let me die! Please!

25:59.859 --> 26:01.420
How do you think Renn felt, shithead?

26:01.422 --> 26:04.742
Please, do... do something! Please!

26:04.744 --> 26:07.824
Check it out, he's pissing himself.

26:07.826 --> 26:10.793
- Oh, shit, man.
- [Laughter]

26:10.795 --> 26:14.130
Ooh. [Laughing]

26:14.132 --> 26:16.733
[Laughter continues]

26:16.735 --> 26:19.669
Saline. Salt and water.

26:19.671 --> 26:21.304
A little tea for coloring.

26:21.306 --> 26:25.108
[Panting]

26:25.110 --> 26:27.877
Whoo. [Laughs]

26:31.470 --> 26:34.017
You still owe Renn for what you took.

26:34.218 --> 26:38.388
6 grand plus $800 for the coke tonight.

26:38.664 --> 26:43.726
Get it here, we'll let you live, okay?

26:43.728 --> 26:46.663
Make a call.

26:55.839 --> 26:58.841
[Dialing cellphone]

26:58.843 --> 27:01.444
[Breathing heavily]

27:01.446 --> 27:04.881
[Line rings]

27:04.883 --> 27:07.350
[Ring]

27:07.352 --> 27:08.721
- Paul: How did they break in exactly?
- [Police radio chatter]

27:08.723 --> 27:10.097
Lydia: They said they came
in through the back door.

27:10.099 --> 27:12.228
They broke one of those glasses.
I always worried... [Gasp]

27:12.230 --> 27:13.628
- Oh.
- Oh, my God.

27:13.630 --> 27:15.252
- Lydia: [Gasps] Oh!
- They got the computer!

27:15.254 --> 27:16.023
- Nicky: Oh, my God.
- They took the television.

27:16.025 --> 27:17.023
Everything is...

27:17.025 --> 27:18.888
- Oh, my God.
- I don't believe it.

27:18.890 --> 27:20.292
Officer, they came in
through... How did they come in?

27:20.294 --> 27:22.375
No. No, not my briefcase.

27:22.377 --> 27:24.338
Please tell me they did
not take my briefcase.

27:24.340 --> 27:26.373
Oh, my God. I'm gonna check upstairs,

27:26.375 --> 27:28.462
- see if they took anything.
- Paul: Look for my briefcase!

27:28.464 --> 27:30.981
Lydia: Okay, Sweetie. Oh, my God! Paul!

27:30.983 --> 27:32.575
Nicky: Check my room!

27:32.577 --> 27:35.250
[Indistinct shouting]

27:38.245 --> 27:39.846
[Knock on door]

27:44.461 --> 27:46.062
[Door unlocks]

27:46.064 --> 27:47.630
[Door creaks]

27:47.632 --> 27:49.988
- I'm here for Craig.
- Scottie: Who are you?

27:49.990 --> 27:51.267
His mother.

27:51.269 --> 27:53.135
[Door closes]

27:58.608 --> 28:01.877
You called your mom?

28:17.761 --> 28:20.262
What'd you do, Baby?

28:20.264 --> 28:23.032
Ripped off our cousin and left her to die.

28:26.710 --> 28:28.077
Craig?

28:47.124 --> 28:51.060
[Zipties clacking]

28:51.062 --> 28:53.513
[Whispers] Thank you.

28:53.515 --> 28:55.716
- [Loud smack]
- Brandon: Oh, shit.

29:08.321 --> 29:10.270
Go get dressed, Baby.

29:20.023 --> 29:23.325
You can put your gun away, <i>pendejo.</i>

29:23.327 --> 29:25.895
Nobody's shootin' anybody here.

29:25.897 --> 29:29.331
He started it. We just made it right.

29:29.333 --> 29:31.409
So we're even?

29:31.411 --> 29:33.077
No.

29:38.377 --> 29:40.745
Craig, give me your keys.

29:41.945 --> 29:44.914
Your keys.

29:44.916 --> 29:48.403
- [Keys jangle]
- That's my Ducati.

29:48.405 --> 29:50.015
What are you doing? Don't give him my bike.

29:50.017 --> 29:53.027
Misbehave, you lose your toys.

29:53.029 --> 29:55.229
Go get in the car.

29:59.563 --> 30:02.031
[Door opens]

30:02.033 --> 30:04.233
[Door closes]

30:06.262 --> 30:10.165
Don't you mistake my
generosity for weakness.

30:12.509 --> 30:13.776
[Thud]

30:16.646 --> 30:19.215
[Door opens]

30:19.217 --> 30:20.649
[Door closes]

30:22.419 --> 30:26.088
<i>[Gunfire on TV]</i>

30:29.307 --> 30:30.793
- Got your shirt.
- <i>[Engine revving]</i>

30:30.795 --> 30:32.695
Thanks.

30:32.697 --> 30:35.698
<i>[Gunfire continues]</i>

30:38.335 --> 30:41.003
Did, um...

30:41.005 --> 30:43.239
did you rob Nicky's house?

30:43.241 --> 30:46.809
I heard you and Craig talking
about it. Was it Nicky's?

30:46.811 --> 30:49.487
[Exhales] So what if it was?

30:51.448 --> 30:53.902
You could've robbed anybody, man.

30:53.904 --> 30:57.820
Look, man, I'm just the grunt, okay?

30:57.822 --> 31:01.724
[Inhales sharply] Talk to Baz.
He's the big man with the plan.

31:03.827 --> 31:05.088
<i>[Gunfire continues]</i>

31:05.090 --> 31:07.624
He's not done with them. [Sniffs]

31:18.542 --> 31:20.009
[Engine turns off]

31:20.011 --> 31:21.844
[Dog barking in distance]

31:21.846 --> 31:24.113
First Pope, now you?

31:24.115 --> 31:27.149
You know I had hoped that
someday you boys would know

31:27.151 --> 31:29.118
how to take care of yourselves.

31:29.120 --> 31:31.120
You haven't even heard my side.

31:31.122 --> 31:34.390
I know your side, Sweetie, by heart.

31:37.727 --> 31:43.065
I encouraged you to be
wild, but there's a line.

31:44.901 --> 31:47.503
[Voice breaks] What do you expect?

31:47.505 --> 31:50.973
All you give me are the shit jobs.

31:50.975 --> 31:52.474
That's not true.

31:52.476 --> 31:55.444
You think I'm stupid?

31:55.446 --> 31:58.514
You don't even <i>try</i> to hide it.

32:00.050 --> 32:02.518
I don't think you're stupid.

32:04.554 --> 32:07.089
I think you've got real gifts.

32:07.091 --> 32:10.059
Yeah? What?

32:11.761 --> 32:14.430
You're fearless.

32:14.432 --> 32:18.300
You've got what it takes to
do things your brothers won't.

32:18.302 --> 32:20.169
They can't.

32:20.171 --> 32:23.505
But the next time
something like this happens,

32:23.507 --> 32:27.376
don't you call me,

32:27.378 --> 32:29.712
because I will not come.

32:32.415 --> 32:34.783
[Car door opens]

32:37.020 --> 32:38.654
[Car door closes]

32:46.396 --> 32:48.664
[Exhales]

32:50.867 --> 32:54.937
[Crickets chirping]

33:14.991 --> 33:18.093
Want some syrup?

33:18.095 --> 33:21.263
Here we go. Just a little bit.

33:21.265 --> 33:23.799
Good? More?

33:25.902 --> 33:27.676
More? Oh, my God.

33:27.678 --> 33:29.805
You're gonna be bouncing
off the walls, kiddo.

33:29.807 --> 33:31.473
- [Refrigerator door closes]
- Yikes.

33:33.643 --> 33:35.878
- We should do this more often.
- Yeah.

33:35.880 --> 33:39.201
Pancakes every day. Remember?

33:39.203 --> 33:40.949
I do remember.

33:40.951 --> 33:44.553
We were kids when we agreed to that.

33:44.555 --> 33:47.656
- A deal's a deal.
- [Chuckles]

33:47.658 --> 33:49.966
That's only 'cause we thought
that's what real parents did.

33:49.968 --> 33:51.293
What's real parents?

33:51.295 --> 33:53.422
Something me and her
sure as hell didn't have.

33:53.424 --> 33:54.768
- Baz...
- What? She should know

33:54.770 --> 33:56.251
where she came from.

33:56.253 --> 33:58.434
[Seabirds calling in distance]

33:58.436 --> 34:01.503
You remember what else we agreed to?

34:01.505 --> 34:03.505
- No?
- Mnh-mnh.

34:03.507 --> 34:06.909
One girl, one boy.

34:06.911 --> 34:09.496
We can't afford another kid.

34:09.498 --> 34:11.213
Well, I'm workin 'on that.

34:11.215 --> 34:13.143
What do you say after this next job,

34:13.145 --> 34:14.983
we take off to the mountains?

34:14.985 --> 34:20.022
Get a cabin like we used to?

34:20.024 --> 34:22.192
What do you say, Lena?
You want a baby brother?

34:22.194 --> 34:23.625
You do? See, she does.

34:23.627 --> 34:25.761
Oh, it's kinda hard to guarantee a boy.

34:25.763 --> 34:28.230
[Clicks tongue] Deal's a deal.

34:30.567 --> 34:32.801
All right, I gotta split.

34:32.803 --> 34:34.902
Bye.

34:34.905 --> 34:37.473
Have a good day at work, Daddy.

34:37.475 --> 34:39.507
- Bye.
- Bye.

34:45.614 --> 34:47.516
[Birds chirping]

34:47.518 --> 34:49.451
[Gate whirring open]

34:54.491 --> 34:57.826
Hey. I brought my bikini.

34:57.828 --> 35:00.363
Nicky, I don't think we
should see each other anymore.

35:00.365 --> 35:01.597
[Scoffs]

35:01.599 --> 35:05.488
Cops said there isn't much chance of
getting our stuff back. Thanks a lot.

35:05.490 --> 35:07.592
Think Smurf can make me a Bloody Mary?

35:07.594 --> 35:09.361
- [Kisses]
- I mean it.

35:11.975 --> 35:13.909
What are you talking about?

35:16.112 --> 35:17.579
[Lowered voice] I'm sorry.

35:19.482 --> 35:22.918
Wait, you're... you're breaking up with me?

35:22.920 --> 35:26.088
- But you like me.
- [Sighs]

35:26.090 --> 35:28.490
- Did I do something?
- No. No.

35:28.492 --> 35:31.593
Is there some other
girl? What? Say something.

35:31.595 --> 35:33.349
Nicky, you have to go.

35:33.351 --> 35:34.792
Look, I know it's been hard for you...

35:34.794 --> 35:36.918
- You have to go.
- Hey, you walk away from me?

35:36.920 --> 35:38.033
Hey, this is bullshit!

35:38.035 --> 35:40.093
You just went out to dinner with my family.

35:40.095 --> 35:42.217
Is that it? [Sniffles] Dinner? Ice cream?

35:42.219 --> 35:44.973
Things get a little too normal for you?

35:44.975 --> 35:47.810
- What's that supposed to mean?
- Your idea of normal

35:47.812 --> 35:50.077
was watching some random guy
stick a needle in your mom

35:50.079 --> 35:51.713
before he put his dick inside her.

35:51.715 --> 35:53.649
- Don't say shit about my mom.
- [Thud]

35:53.651 --> 35:57.386
[Breathing heavily]

35:57.388 --> 36:00.556
[Whispering] You don't
know what's going on here.

36:00.558 --> 36:03.192
You have no idea.

36:03.194 --> 36:04.783
[Voice breaks] Why are
you acting like this?

36:04.785 --> 36:06.047
- No.
- Why?

36:06.049 --> 36:08.497
Look...

36:08.499 --> 36:10.332
it's over.

36:10.334 --> 36:13.035
[Breathing heavily]

36:13.037 --> 36:16.438
I want you to stay away from me,

36:16.440 --> 36:19.374
and you stay away from my family.

36:35.191 --> 36:37.893
[Door opens and closes]

36:47.270 --> 36:49.371
[Utensils clink]

36:49.373 --> 36:51.740
Smurf: Lunch!

36:54.043 --> 36:55.577
[Groans, sighs]

36:55.829 --> 36:58.480
Hey, buddy. How was last night? A rager?

36:58.482 --> 37:01.617
[Inhales deeply]

37:01.834 --> 37:05.195
- What?
- Renn's party.

37:05.197 --> 37:06.364
It was okay.

37:06.366 --> 37:09.224
By the way you made it sound,
I thought you'd still be high.

37:11.361 --> 37:13.962
- [Dish clatters]
- What are you building out there?

37:13.964 --> 37:15.230
A fountain.

37:15.232 --> 37:17.165
What? For, like, birds?

37:17.167 --> 37:19.468
For, like, me.

37:19.470 --> 37:23.738
Here you go, Sweetie. It's your favorite.

37:23.740 --> 37:25.452
Spicy chili.

37:30.532 --> 37:32.346
- Craig's looks good.
- What the hell, man?

37:32.348 --> 37:34.307
- Just take mine.
- I don't want yours.

37:34.309 --> 37:35.584
Pope: Don't make a big deal about this.

37:35.586 --> 37:37.396
[Mouth full] Oh, my God. If
it get you guys to shut up,

37:37.398 --> 37:39.264
- I'll have yours.
- Fine.

37:55.140 --> 37:56.741
You hungry, Sweetie?

38:10.614 --> 38:12.715
What's the matter, honey?

38:15.943 --> 38:17.877
Nicky broke up with me.

38:20.430 --> 38:22.631
Do you know why?

38:37.667 --> 38:40.231
Wow, you weren't kidding. This
stuff is <i>really</i> good.

38:40.233 --> 38:42.651
- Yeah, it's great.
- Aged 18 years.

38:42.653 --> 38:45.426
After I heard what happened, I
figured you could use a drink.

38:45.428 --> 38:47.047
- Can you believe it?
- [Laughs] I can't.

38:47.049 --> 38:48.668
Cops said that a bunch
of amateurs did this.

38:48.670 --> 38:51.465
- Yeah.
- They still have nothing to go off of.

38:51.467 --> 38:53.467
- You have insurance?
- Yeah.

38:53.469 --> 38:55.536
Yeah. That sucks.

38:55.538 --> 38:58.218
It's just stuff, though,
right? It's replaceable.

38:58.220 --> 39:00.808
[Sighs]

39:00.810 --> 39:03.044
They took my briefcase.

39:03.046 --> 39:04.991
- Why?
- It was locked.

39:04.993 --> 39:07.715
They probably thought there
was something valuable inside?

39:07.717 --> 39:08.926
I-I-I
don't know.

39:08.928 --> 39:11.952
But it's just work stuff, right? I mean...

39:11.954 --> 39:14.522
What's the problem?

39:14.524 --> 39:16.724
Some of those files are classified.

39:16.726 --> 39:18.402
Okay, they're not supposed
to be off the base.

39:18.404 --> 39:21.180
I mean, I bring them home sometimes because

39:21.182 --> 39:23.280
I'd spend the rest of my
life in that freaking office.

39:23.282 --> 39:25.796
- I know. I hear ya.
- [Sighs]

39:25.798 --> 39:28.369
The Navy takes this shit so seriously.

39:28.371 --> 39:30.137
Wait. Would they fire you?

39:30.139 --> 39:33.441
- They could court-martial me.
- Oh, shit.

39:35.744 --> 39:37.211
[Clicks tongue]

39:41.016 --> 39:44.118
How bad do you want those files back?

39:44.120 --> 39:46.187
What's that supposed to mean?

39:46.189 --> 39:48.537
Well, we handle a bunch
of low income properties,

39:48.539 --> 39:50.371
and we deal with some
pretty shady characters.

39:50.373 --> 39:53.694
If we want a problem fixed...

39:53.696 --> 39:56.030
we call some guys.

39:56.032 --> 39:58.032
What kind of guys?

39:58.034 --> 39:59.761
The kind of guys that can ask around.

39:59.763 --> 40:02.920
They can find out which
crew did your house.

40:02.922 --> 40:04.923
Maybe get your briefcase back.

40:04.925 --> 40:06.407
How are they gonna do that?

40:06.409 --> 40:09.610
[Chuckles] It's better
not to ask questions.

40:14.325 --> 40:15.497
Forget it. I shouldn't have brought it up.

40:15.499 --> 40:17.132
No. No, no, no.

40:19.345 --> 40:21.822
Call your guys.

40:21.909 --> 40:23.275
Okay.

40:25.694 --> 40:29.230
[Seabirds calling, door closes]

40:29.232 --> 40:31.891
- Hey.
- What are you doing here?

40:31.893 --> 40:34.060
I was just having a drink with your dad.

40:34.062 --> 40:37.471
Don't tell J I saw you. He
might go off on you, too.

40:37.473 --> 40:38.669
What does that mean?

40:38.671 --> 40:40.638
He's a shit is what it means.

40:43.779 --> 40:45.813
He just broke up with me.

40:47.716 --> 40:49.650
- Why?
- Like I know?

40:49.652 --> 40:51.074
Everything was cool,
and then out of nowhere,

40:51.106 --> 40:53.885
he just flips out and
wants nothing to do with me.

40:55.119 --> 40:57.053
I should've punched him.

40:59.222 --> 41:01.162
Well, he made a big mistake.

41:01.164 --> 41:04.298
♪♪

41:13.875 --> 41:17.244
[Cellphone rings]

41:17.246 --> 41:20.047
[Ring]

41:20.049 --> 41:22.554
[Ring]

41:22.556 --> 41:24.327
- Hey, Baz.
- <i>Hey, man, you free?</i>

41:24.329 --> 41:26.066
<i>Do you wanna grab a beer?</i>

41:26.068 --> 41:27.954
Uh, yeah. Yeah, sure. Where?

41:27.956 --> 41:32.393
<i>How about Tower 9? Say half an hour?</i>

41:32.395 --> 41:34.743
- Okay, cool.
- <i>All right, great, I'll see you there.</i>

41:34.745 --> 41:37.832
Right, yeah. Okay, bye.

41:37.834 --> 41:41.869
[Seabirds calling]

41:43.505 --> 41:46.040
[Clack]

41:46.042 --> 41:48.209
[Door bangs]

41:48.211 --> 41:50.578
Have you seen the diamond blade?

41:54.716 --> 41:58.786
I've been putting these in your food

41:58.788 --> 42:02.990
because you need them and you
never would've listened to me,

42:02.992 --> 42:06.393
not in the state you were in.

42:06.395 --> 42:09.630
So I should thank you.

42:09.632 --> 42:13.501
The instructions are on the labels.

42:13.503 --> 42:17.471
You know you could've gotten
me sent back to prison.

42:17.473 --> 42:19.459
Before your next piss test,

42:19.461 --> 42:22.161
you tell your parole officer
you're back on your meds.

42:22.163 --> 42:24.420
And what makes you think
I'm gonna keep taking 'em?

42:24.422 --> 42:27.815
Because you know you need them.

42:36.791 --> 42:41.395
You don't like me unless
I'm on these pills?

42:41.397 --> 42:44.231
Is that it?

42:47.602 --> 42:50.371
- Or I could just flush 'em.
- [Pills rattle]

42:50.373 --> 42:53.574
Could take 'em or flush 'em.

42:53.576 --> 42:55.743
So many choices.

43:02.918 --> 43:04.818
[Cabinet door opens]

43:07.722 --> 43:10.758
[Seabirds calling]

43:21.436 --> 43:22.836
Hey, man.

43:22.838 --> 43:25.205
Hey.

43:25.207 --> 43:26.907
I heard about Nicky.

43:26.909 --> 43:29.677
Oh, yeah. Did Smurf tell you?

43:29.679 --> 43:33.980
Mm-hmm. I thought things were good.

43:33.982 --> 43:36.057
Me, too, man.

43:36.059 --> 43:38.986
Not for her, I guess.

43:38.988 --> 43:41.088
So she dumped you?

43:41.090 --> 43:42.523
Yeah.

43:42.525 --> 43:44.825
I had no idea it was coming, man.

43:46.795 --> 43:49.797
[Sighs heavily] Yeah, women
don't always make sense.

43:51.366 --> 43:53.752
Thing is...

43:53.754 --> 43:55.620
Nicky told me you dumped <i>her.</i>

43:58.139 --> 44:00.641
So which is it, J?

44:02.110 --> 44:05.045
How 'bout you don't bullshit
me, I don't bullshit you?

44:05.047 --> 44:07.781
You figured out what's been going on?

44:07.783 --> 44:09.717
Yeah, enough.

44:09.719 --> 44:12.386
And you think you're protecting her?

44:12.388 --> 44:14.555
- You're using her, right?
- Yes.

44:14.557 --> 44:15.823
And her dad.

44:15.825 --> 44:16.955
I thought you'd know this by now.

44:17.014 --> 44:20.251
Everyone outside the
family is a mark. Everyone.

44:20.253 --> 44:21.829
Am I a mark?

44:21.831 --> 44:23.764
[Laughs]

44:23.766 --> 44:25.555
Look, you overreacted. It's fine.

44:25.557 --> 44:26.837
You didn't do any permanent damage.

44:26.839 --> 44:30.135
But this thing is happening, okay?

44:30.137 --> 44:32.906
With or without you, this is happening.

44:32.908 --> 44:34.875
Just leave Nicky and her family alone.

44:34.877 --> 44:37.349
Are you making demands now?
You think that's how this works?

44:37.351 --> 44:39.803
You're lucky you and I
are just talking right now.

44:39.805 --> 44:41.438
You're <i>lucky.</i>

44:44.919 --> 44:48.555
Family comes first.
Everything else is second.

44:48.557 --> 44:50.257
You understand me?

44:53.128 --> 44:57.431
I need to know you're not
gonna do anything stupid.

44:57.433 --> 44:59.633
Are you gonna do anything stupid, J?

44:59.635 --> 45:02.002
No.

45:02.004 --> 45:06.440
I wanna believe you. I really, really do.

45:06.793 --> 45:08.677
I'll see you back at the house.

45:29.597 --> 45:30.789
[Sighs]

45:30.791 --> 45:34.568
I told Pope about the medications.

45:34.570 --> 45:37.271
I had no choice. And don't worry.

45:37.273 --> 45:39.773
I didn't tell him you knew anything.

45:42.944 --> 45:44.445
Where is he?

45:44.447 --> 45:46.947
In his hotel room, I hope.

45:48.717 --> 45:51.051
We may have another problem.

45:51.053 --> 45:52.920
Nicky's dad?

45:52.922 --> 45:55.556
No, that went just like we wanted it to.

45:55.558 --> 45:57.424
[Inhales deeply]

46:00.862 --> 46:02.362
J.

46:10.905 --> 46:13.006
[Exhales deeply]

46:13.008 --> 46:16.043
[Crickets chirping]

46:29.424 --> 46:31.191
[Knocks on door]

46:33.595 --> 46:36.630
[Breathing heavily]

46:44.672 --> 46:47.307
[Knocks loudly]

46:50.245 --> 46:52.646
[Door opens]

46:52.798 --> 46:54.574
Hey. Is everything okay?

46:54.628 --> 46:56.850
I was worried when I didn't hear from you.

46:56.852 --> 46:59.353
I'm sorry. I just, um...

47:00.468 --> 47:02.903
Hey, what's... what is it? What's wrong?

47:05.593 --> 47:07.828
Can I come in for a little while?

47:07.830 --> 47:11.098
Yeah. Yeah, of course. Come on.

47:15.398 --> 47:18.534
[Door creaks]

